Situacija je bila sprovod bližnje osobe. Pomogli su mi prijatelji koji su mi davali podršku.

Plakanje je zapravo bilo potaknuto plakanjem prijateljice i situacijom u kojoj se nalazila (izrazito bezobrazno ponašanje njezinog bivšeg dečka i velika patnja koju je to njoj uzrokovalo). Bile smo u njezinom stanu (dnevnom boravku). Osjećala sam se izrazito tužno zbog nje, ali i bijesno zbog osobe koja ju je dovela u takvo stanje. Također bespomoćno jer je ona bila neutješna. Pomogle smo jedna drugoj utjehom u obliku zagrljaja.

Zadnji put sam plakala kad mi je dečko priznao da mi je lagao u vezi nekih svojih problematičnih ponašanja, konkretno u vezi svog kockanja. To je bio prvi put da mi je išta slagao jer zaista imamo lijep iskren odnos te mi je to teško palo. Bila sam s njim u svom stanu te me on na kraju i utješio i uspjeli smo riješiti tu situaciju.
Plakanje je uzrokovala svađa sa dečkom. Bila sam u trgovačkom centru, a osjećala sam se isfrustrirano. Utješila me prijateljica
Plakala sam zbog frustracija na radnome mjestu i nemogućnosti organiziranja vremena. Sjedila sam u stanu, u dnevnom boravku, dok me dečko pokušavao utješiti.

Bila sam u dnevnoj sobi, moje plakanje je uzrokovalo to što se jedan poznanik prije nekoliko dana ubio, u tom trenutku sam razgovarala sa sestrom, no nije me tješila. Osjećala sam se tužno jer je jedan mladi život završio na takav način. Plakala sam desetak minuta i nakon toga sam se osjećala uobičajeno. Također, prije toga sam se osjećala uobićajeno, sestrina priča o njemu me rasplakala.

U školi njemačkog, jedna je učenica uvijek iznimno bezobrazna prema meni, bez nekog očitog razloga, te verbalno i neverbalno (puhanjem, ismijavanjem ili okretanjem očiju) komentira svaku moju radnju. Prošli tjedan me to dovelo do plača, a pomogla je profesorica koja prije takvo ponašanje nije uočila, ali ga isto ne želi tolerirati.

Uzrok plakanja bio je prekid romantične veze s dečkom. Iako smo obje znali što slijedi taj dan kad smo se našli da popričao o nekim stvarima, ova me je situacija izrazito pogodila. Situacija se odvijala u kafiću, ali je plakanje nastupilo kasnije, u autu (na putu kući) i doma. Prije samog razgovora bila sam nervozna, anksiozna, tužna. Nakon razgovora prevladasla je tuga i osjećaj bespomoćnosti,usamljenosti. Ironično, najveća podrška mi je bio upravo bivši dečko koji se pobrinuo da dođem sigurno doma, provjerio je drugi dan jesam li dobro i sl. i trudio se da unatoč tome ostanemo u dobrim odnosima.

Zadnja situacija u kojoj sam se našla da sam plakala bila ja pred nekoliko dana, zbog toga što se dečko odeslio u stranu zemlju zbog zapošljavanja i njegovog unapređenja. Te tako osjećam potrebu da mi nedostaje

qual_Q: The last time i cried was when I climbed the highest point of the Himalayas as I reached 4800m and was trekking for 5 hours so I felt tired and exhausted. When i reached the highest point, I dropped to the floor and was comforted by a friend who let me cry on their lap for 5 minutes.

I was being asked to leave a pub after ordering food because one of my friends had been wrongly accused of possession of cannabis. The manager was refusing me a refund and telling us to leave immediately because my friend was smoking a herb to help him quit smoking. The irony and injustice of the situation as well as the stubborn attitude of the manager left me feeling extremely frustrated and angry. After I just regretted not calling the police and felt exploited. I was comforted by a group of friends but noone had seen me shed a tear.

I cried because I was giving some advice to my girlfriend about how to cope with someone dying, as a family friend had recently died, and this brought back memories of how i felt after my granddad died 2 years back. I was in bed talking to my girlfriend who comforted me, and I felt tired afterwards
It was 'Christopher Robin' and it was a few days before me and my girlfriend were going to be separated from each other for 10 months.
Remembering bad memories from that had happened in the past year. I was helped by one of my friends as we just chatted and ate food.
my grandmother died, i was at the funeral, i was feeling sad before and after, my family was there for support, also my friends and colleages supported me later on
Death of a family friend. I was at home, I felt shocked before, and down after. And my family helped me

My parents had decided to move away from each other and were planning to divorce, while at approximately the same time one of my grandparents died. Primarily due to uncertainty regarding the future and the fact that I had been alone in my flat for several weeks, I felt somewhat helpless and powerless during the experience, leading to a crying experience one night.

I do not cry much, so it would've been years ago when I was in school. I have a chest deformity and I was mobbed by people in the school who were enquiring about it. They were not making fun of me but the attention made me cry for some reason. I think it was caused by my sensitivity about my deformity. 

I recall feeling the fragility of being a teenager before I was about the cry, and afterwards I felt embarrassed that I had cried.

Some people did ask if I was OK when I cried, but it occurred at the end of a lesson and the people around me dissipated immediately after.

After going up for a promotion in my job after hitting all my targets in the year i was made redundant. The reason was that many co-workers , whom I considered friends were complaining about me , claiming I distract them all with innapropriate and stupid talk. When I got home I cried , feeling angry and distressed. Nobody was there to comfort me.
At first I was feeling anxious but then when I got to the home which houses my grandad ( he has dementia) I cried a little, my uncle comforted me.

At my grandad's funeral, it was the only time I've cried from a negative emotion in about 10 years. The whole day was very intense, and very emotional for everyone. Me and my sister's comforted each other.

I was breaking up with my girlfriend at the time and I was awash with feelings of sadness and guilt. I was in bedroom and it was late at night. Before it happened I felt very anxious because I knew it wasn’t going to be easy. Afterwards I felt empty, I knew that life was changing but I didn’t know if it was for better or for worse. It took a few days for that numb feeling to go away. Speaking to friends and family helped but not in a huge way as I had gone over all their points in my head already.

The first time i saw my passed granddad in the mortuary. the feeling i felt before was a feeling of strange calmness. i attribute this to the shock of the whole experience, however once i actually saw him i broke down.  i was comforted by my uncles who were around me which calmed me down for sure.

Lost a family member last year. We were very close so it upset me when they passed away. They were ill towards the end but they had been for a long time before as well so we weren't expecting them to pass away that day. I had been expecting but not at the same time because they pulled through before. When I found out I was heartbroken. I had the close support of my family and friends to get me through it.

I was untruthful to my partner and when the lie was exposed the guilt caused me to cry and become very emotional. I wasnt helped by anyone as I was in the wrong. Afterwards I felt relief that it all came out.

I had recently broken up with my fiance and had recently started a new job, which was not really working out and coupled with the situation with my fiance, I felt very overwhelmed and lost. I did not feel much better afterwards, I was with my parents who helped comfort me.
when I lost my father. I was in my home country Ghana. I felt helpless. I was comforted by my sister and other family members.
Breakup
Suffered a loss. Family and work were supportive. Work gave me some time off.

The death of my family dog. I had it when I was a teen, and although I moved away and left it with my parents, after coming back from serving abroad in the military he was a real source of stability for me as I readjusted to civilian life. I didn't realise just how much until he was gone. I broke down and cried in the vets as he was put to sleep, and honestly not sure if I've felt better since. Feels like there's a massive weight now.
Grandfather passed away
On a night out, argument, felt upset and angry afterwards.

break up of relationship

Stress and my boyfriend was there to comfort me.
Falling out with a friend, at a nightclub . Felt happy before and angry after.
The last time I cried was due to someone questioning their trust in me making me feel rubbish and after extensive time trying to persuade them i felt as though i was not getting anywhere

I last cried after receiving some negative news about a family member. I felt very sad for a while. I was comforted by my friend.
I was in my flat kitchen, I felt very vulnerable - I was comforted by my two flat mates, one boy and one girl
leaving a club, being in a stressful situation with the noise and lights, felt very claustrophobic and stresssed out, someone came out just after to me, afterwards felt calmer
I have family issues and I had an online session with my psychologist to whom i explained an unfortunate event which made me cry.

Recently went into a store and tried on an item of clothing. I am normally a small and here I was supposedly a large. As weight is a sensitive topic for me and most girls my age it caused me to cry. My mother helped me in this instance.

Mainly because someone who was drunk was telling me real thoughts whilst I was sober , quite deep thoughts which made me feel absolutely sad speechless but sad because I didn’t even know what to say but cry. I received comfort from a friend though who told me not to worry which was good!

I had a cold and two people from my student accommodation were being treated for meningitis so I was getting super paranoid on top of general uni stress and starting to miss home. I was alone in my flat at uni and I felt pretty rubbish before and after. I face timed my mum multiple times during the day and hung out in my friends flat to keep my mind off it afterwards

Grief, I've recently lost both my great grandparents who I was caring for. I cry about it most days and tjis usually happens whenever im alone. The only person who really helps is my boyfriend, I can't talk to family as I don't want to upset them.
